      .medium-8.columns
        h2 Diana Rodgers
        p Diana Rodgers is a farmer, nutritionist, and best‐selling author of Paleo Lunches and Breakfasts on the Go and The Homegrown Paleo Cookbook. On her blog, Sustainable Dish, and local television show of the same name, she explores which foods are optimal for human nutrition, the environment, animal welfare and social justice. Diana also coproduces the podcast Modern Farm Girls with Liz Wolfe and produces short films on sustainable agriculture. She has been featured in The Los Angeles Times, The Boston Globe, Mother Earth News, Edible Boston, and is a staff writer for Paleo Magazine. She lives at Clark Organic Farm in Carlisle, Massachusetts which runs a vegetable and meat CSA, plus operates a farm stand, runs education programs to local schools and colleges, and hosts interns from around the world looking to learn about sustainable agriculture.

