      .medium-8.columns
        h2 Dr. Richard Teague
        p Dr. Richard Teague is a research scientist with the Texas A&M University System. He uses a systems approach in his research by working with leading conservation ranchers who are able to regenerate ecosystem function and improve their livelihoods. His aim is to determine the extent that livestock producers can use different grazing management strategies to mitigate and adapt to alternative climate change scenarios.

  #finian
  section.main
    .row
      .medium-4.columns
        img(src='/assets/images/event/speakers/finian.png')

      .medium-8.columns
        h2 Finian Makepeace

        p Finian Makepeace is the co­founder and Policy Chair of Kiss the Ground. He is a recording artis and his passion for soil came after learning that the loss of topsoil (humus) plays a major role in climate change, drought, and the nutrition of our food. He loves telling "the soil story", especially the part about what can happen when we build it back through Regenerative Agriculture.
        p Through  media,  policy  and  education,  his  none­profit  Kiss  The  Ground,  is  committed  to connecting  culture  to  agriculture.  Their  mission  is  to  inspire  and  advocate  for  soil restoration worldwide.  They  help  farmers  and  communities  rebuild  soil  through  policy  and  consumer awareness. As Director of the policy department Finian works at the local (Los Angeles), State (California)  and Federal  level. His primary focus  is to bring NGO's  and government  agencies together to assist in developing strategies and programs to build back soil.
        p Most  recently,  with  the  launch  of  The  Soil  Story,  Finian  ran  a  campaign  petition  urging  the California legislature to allocate 160 million from the Greenhouse Gas Reduction Fund to a state Healthy Soil's Budget.
        p Finian's hope is that this year, "The International Year of Soil", the whole world falls in love with soil.

  #haven
  section.main
